---
import MainLayout from '../../layouts/MainLayout.astro';
---

<MainLayout
  title="McMaster-Carr"
  description="Supply chain operations, ergonomics coaching, and process improvement experience at McMaster-Carr."
>
  <section class="hero">
    <p class="eyebrow">Experience</p>

    <h1>McMaster-Carr</h1>

    <p class="intro">
      Supported supply chain operations within a highly standardized
      distribution environment while contributing to workplace safety,
      ergonomics, and process improvement initiatives across a workforce of
      approximately 500 employees.
    </p>

    <p class="meta">
      Supply Chain Operations Associate & Ergonomic Coach • February 2020 –
      March 2022
    </p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Overview</h2>

    <p>
      McMaster-Carr is known for its operational excellence, attention to
      detail, and commitment to serving customers accurately and efficiently.
      Working within this environment exposed me to the importance of
      standardized processes, quality control, safety, and continuous
      improvement at scale.
    </p>

    <p>
      During my time there, I supported high-volume order fulfillment
      operations, managed material traceability requirements, processed custom
      material orders, and later served as an Ergonomic Coach focused on
      employee safety, onboarding, and injury prevention.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Supply Chain Operations</h2>

    <p>
      As a Supply Chain Operations Associate, I worked in a fast-paced and
      highly organized distribution environment responsible for fulfilling
      hundreds of customer orders each day while maintaining strict accuracy
      standards.
    </p>

    <p>
      Responsibilities included interpreting order specifications, processing
      custom material requests, maintaining material certification and
      traceability documentation, and verifying fulfillment requirements before
      shipment. These activities required strong attention to detail and a
      disciplined approach to quality and consistency.
    </p>

    <p>
      The role also provided exposure to how large-scale distribution systems
      operate, including inventory flow, process standardization, documentation
      control, and customer-focused fulfillment.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Ergonomics & Safety</h2>

    <p>
      In addition to operational responsibilities, I served as an Ergonomic
      Coach responsible for promoting safe work practices and helping employees
      reduce injury risk during daily operations.
    </p>

    <p>
      The role involved conducting regular observation and coaching sessions,
      onboarding new employees into company ergonomics programs, identifying
      workplace risks, and recommending improvements to work habits and task
      execution.
    </p>

    <p>
      Many recommendations focused on reducing repetitive strain and improving
      long-term employee well-being. Examples included optimizing product
      placement to minimize excessive reaching, bending, and lifting while
      encouraging proper movement techniques during repetitive tasks.
    </p>

    <p>
      My goal was not simply to help employees work faster, but to help them
      work safely and sustainably so they could leave work in the same
      condition they arrived.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Operational Excellence</h2>

    <p>
      One of the most valuable aspects of working at McMaster-Carr was learning
      how small decisions can create significant downstream consequences when
      repeated hundreds or thousands of times. Accuracy, organization, and
      consistency were treated as essential components of every process.
    </p>

    <p>
      Through ergonomics and safety initiatives, I collaborated with teams
      across four distribution centers to share observations, discuss emerging
      trends, and exchange best practices. These discussions helped improve
      operational consistency while reinforcing a culture of continuous
      improvement.
    </p>

    <p>
      The experience demonstrated how effective systems balance efficiency,
      quality, safety, and the needs of the people performing the work.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Key Takeaways</h2>

    <p>
      McMaster-Carr reinforced the importance of process discipline, attention
      to detail, and continuous improvement. Working within a highly
      standardized operation taught me that small mistakes can become
      significant problems when repeated at scale, making consistency and
      accuracy critical to long-term success.
    </p>

    <p>
      The experience also influenced how I think about leadership and system
      design. Strong processes should not only achieve operational goals, but
      also support the people responsible for executing them. This perspective
      later influenced how I approached employee development, process design,
      and business operations in subsequent roles.
    </p>
  </section>
</MainLayout>

<style>
  section + section {
    margin-top: 4rem;
  }

  .hero {
    max-width: 48rem;
  }

  .intro {
    font-size: 1.125rem;
  }

  .meta {
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    margin-top: 1rem;
    font-size: 0.95rem;
  }
</style>